definitions.name: 7fd30824-e20c-473e-b906-f4f30ebc4bb0
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Biotic charger that can travel to enemies in the blink of an eye, then deal point-blank damage.

The Human Vanguard is a talented Alliance veteran who hopes he can relive his glory days in Andromeda. He often gives advice to the younger members of the team and loves to say, "I told you so."

definitions.name: 32672912-52e6-43f0-a717-f850d1799c44
definitions.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Explosives technician with high survivability and area damage.

This is great! Who knew all those science lessons she had to take would be so handy? If only she could brag to her friends back home about her cool new team and how much fun fighting these little kett guys is.

definitions.name: b2e2cd83-028b-4b51-b088-6fa3fe6146eb
definitions.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: Weapons expert with heavy shields and armor.

To avoid a court martial on Palaven for his role in a massacre, the Turian Soldier went on the lam and worked as a mercenary until he was able to buy his way into the Initiative.

definitions.name: c421b264-cddf-4170-9ca3-296a55a0ec49
definitions.locDescription:
Uncommon Class: A mighty biotic that compensates for light armor with crowd-control attacks and widespread damage. 

An Alliance veteran, the Asari Adept has seen combat before and looks out for the younger members of the team. She enjoys crowd control, and enjoys the sense of satisfaction when the team works well together.

definitions.name: 501b0540-e81f-4522-aa40-21e384347285
definitions.locDescription:
Rare Class: Mobile fighter with biotic powers who can cloak allies. 

In the Milky Way, the Asari Huntress was a well-regarded bounty hunter until she took the wrong job and found herself on the most-wanted list. She joined the Andromeda Initiative to escape her enemies and begin the hunt anew.

definitions.name: e2f76cf1-4b42-4dba-9751-f2add5c3f654
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: A powerful biotic with light armor who uses powers to control crowds and cause widespread damage.

The Human Adept doesn't much care about the romance of settling a new galaxy. What she sees here is a power vacuum—and she's damn well going to fill it.

definitions.name: e4357633-93bc-4596-99c3-4cc0a49b2277
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: A powerful biotic with light armor who uses powers to control crowds and cause widespread damage.

The Human Adept doesn't really talk about why he joined the Initiative; in fact, he doesn't talk much at all. Given the quiet intensity with which he rips through enemies, none of his teammates are rushing to ask about his past.

definitions.name: c756c741-1bc8-47a8-9f35-b7ca943ba034
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Clever tech expert that distracts, limits, and locks down opponents on the battlefield. 

Exuberant and enthusiastic, the Human Engineer loves using creative tech to blow things up. If it does the job and makes a spectacular explosion doing so, that's the best of both worlds.

definitions.name: a3960123-3625-4126-82e4-1f9a127d33aa
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Clever tech expert that distracts, limits, and locks down opponents on the battlefield. 

The Human Engineer was always good at science, but he knows he's got what it takes to be a leader—leaders should be the smart people, after all. He'll be a Pathfinder some day, just you wait and see.

definitions.name: cae8a2f3-fdaf-471c-9391-c29f6d4308c3
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Stealth expert who moves unnoticed around the battlefield with tech powers, then picks off enemies with well-placed shots. 

After losing her husband and child in a botched robbery back in the Milky Way, the Human Infiltrator came to Andromeda for a fresh start. She joined APEX to do some good—and to work through some anger and sadness.

definitions.name: 34aeef66-a030-445e-98e2-1513c0c78df4
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Stealth expert who moves unnoticed around the battlefield with tech powers, then picks off enemies with well-placed shots. 

One of the younger team members, the Human Infiltrator is more thrill-seeker than hardened combatant. His natural abilities make him effective, and his reckless nature can work both for and against him.

definitions.name: 319ffe5d-f8fb-4217-bd2f-2e8af4f53fc8
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Tactical defense expert with sturdy tech armor and a versatile power set. 

Excited to seek adventure, this is the Human Sentinel's first time testing her combat skills in a real-life situation. She's very skilled, and what she lacks in experience, she makes up for in enthusiasm.

definitions.name: baae0381-8690-4097-ae6d-0c16473519b4
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Tactical defense expert with sturdy tech armor and a versatile power set.

The Human Sentinel is a seasoned professional; he's been there and done that. Nothing surprises him, even in a brand-new galaxy.

definitions.name: 79f3511c-55da-67f0-5002-359c370015d8
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Weapons expert with heavy armor and a gun for all occasions. Effective at any range.

The Human Soldier worked private security in the Terminus System, but left to find adventure in Andromeda. She likes getting to know her new APEX colleagues and working with them to get the job done well.

definitions.name: af3a2cf0-dff7-4ca8-9199-73ce546c3e7b
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Weapons expert with heavy armor and a gun for all occasions. Effective at any range.

The Human Soldier worked in the Alliance before joining the Initiative. He likes the idea of helping establish life in a new world, and he wants to do it in the way he thinks is noble and right.

definitions.name: 96fa16c5-9f2b-46f8-a491-a4b0a24a1089
definitions.locDescription:
Common Class: Biotic charger that can travel to enemies in the blink of an eye, then deal point-blank damage. 

The Human Female Vanguard was a respected leader within the Alliance, so Initiative leaders recruited her to organize and establish security organizations in Andromeda. APEX is more than the "segue to eventual retirement" she'd anticipated, but she's good at her job and respected by the team.

definitions.name: eaefec2a-d892-498b-a175-e5d2048ae39a
definitions.locDescription: An explosive projectile launched from an omni-tool that deals massive damage.

definitions.name: af39be6b-0542-4997-b524-227aa41ae2eb
definitions.locDescription: An emergency dose of medi-gel to revive yourself when you're down and out.

definitions.name: 2cc0d932-8e9d-48a6-a6e8-a5665b77e835
definitions.locDescription: Instantly reloads all weapons and fills all reserves with thermal clips and power cells.

definitions.name: 4d790010-1a79-4bd0-a79b-d52cac068a3a
definitions.locDescription: Instantly and fully restores health and shield strength with a mix of medicine and machinery.

definitions.name: d5bf2213-d2d2-f892-7310-c39a15fb2ef3
definitions.locDescription: A common and versatile assault rifle. The M-8 Avenger's modular design and inexpensive components made it a favorite of military groups and mercenaries in the Milky Way. Many Avengers were acquired for Andromeda Initiative security forces. The sturdy rifle has a reputation for being reliable and easy to use.

definitions.name: ef539e69-d0e1-4d9a-9f55-6034a13343d8
definitions.locDescription: The Cyclone's rapid rate of fire requires a short warm up before use. The rifle's mediocre accuracy is balanced by a massive capacity. As its manufacturer states, "With so many rounds to spare, what does it matter if a few don't land?" The Cyclone was removed from production years prior to the Andromeda Initiative's departure due to intense maintenance requirements, but some soldiers still swear by it.

definitions.name: 5d2f2c66-d90f-464b-ab05-801569b6ddc7
definitions.locDescription: The sleek L-89 Halberd favors power and precision. The semi-automatic rifle was the Andromeda Initiative's attempt to make a weapon on par with the reliable M-96 Mattock that also used Initiative breakthroughs in materials science. Only a few were made, but their effectiveness in the field is unquestioned.

definitions.name: 9f2f5947-7674-4da9-9487-460a1fe494f5
definitions.locDescription: Andromeda Initiative engineers developed the automatic X5 Ghost from the baseline M-8 Avenger to make it easier to maintain and modify aboard the arks and the Nexus. The standard rifle for Initiative personnel also possesses recording and sensor functions so it can be left behind as a "black box" by doomed explorers.

definitions.name: 91e16132-5d76-4540-a84b-54ed98bd61b1
definitions.locDescription: The M-25 Hornet is a heavy submachine gun that fires three-round bursts. Originally created in the Milky Way by the paramilitary group Cerberus. The Andromeda Initiative's Hornet stockpile was seized from a Cerberus base by the Systems Alliance, then bought by the Initiative at a semi-legal auction.

definitions.name: 4ccc7f54-791c-4b66-954b-a0bd6496f210
definitions.locDescription: A reliable semi-automatic pistol. Originally manufactured by Elanus Risk Control, the rapid-fire Predator is a deadly and inexpensive weapon. Although Milky Way militaries generally avoided using the Predator, the Andromeda Initiative obtained and adjusted several hundred of them.

definitions.name: e8406e6a-01be-4844-98ed-efcc0e2d6c29
definitions.locDescription: The slow-firing, semi-automatic Talon scatters projectiles like a shotgun. Its waste heat is excessive enough that it requires six separate ammunition blocks that rotate like a twentieth-century revolver to prevent premature melting of the shot.

definitions.name: ca7d0f24-fc19-4a78-9d25-9c84eb01e3a5
definitions.locDescription: The M-23 Katana was a popular shotgun among Milky Way soldiers, criminals, and civilians. It was manufactured by Ariake Technologies, an Earth-based company eager to do business with the Andromeda Initiative.

definitions.name: 22be0636-be99-46c1-9a29-66e5f797e636
definitions.locDescription: The Scattershot fires particle blasts which can focus upon a target at range. This focusing effect is a result of advanced Initiative targeting systems and invisible "tracing" of paths for the Remnant-derived energy beams. The Scattershot does not require reloading, but will overheat from continuous use.

definitions.name: b4f530cd-7dc3-4641-906a-32103cc35f29
definitions.locDescription: Capable of three-shot bursts, the Incisor was part of a new wave of Milky Way sniper rifles designed to overload a foe's defenses. It was advertised as having negligible recoil, though the second and third rounds frequently "climb" in combat conditions, distributing damage along a vertical line.

definitions.name: 38e07595-764b-4d9c-b466-f26c7c416860
definitions.locDescription: The Viper is a rapid-fire rifle popular with military snipers who appreciated a long-range gun that could snap off multiple shots in a short period. Rosenkov Materials sold a considerable number of Vipers to the Initiative at a discount in return for undisclosed favors from Initiative founder Jien Garson.

definitions.name: e27b77d9-06bc-422c-9ac5-46f12510e668
definitions.locDescription: A heavy and formidable single-shot sniper rifle originally designed for use against armored vehicles. The Widows acquired by the Andromeda Initiative have been modified for additional portability—the original model was nearly unusable by organic lifeforms.

definitions.name: d59f6774-f5e9-48c9-ba8c-4766e4f07fab
definitions.locDescription: Enhances a weapon's barrel, creating greater gunfire velocity and impact.

definitions.name: 3815b17a-3e21-4d88-944e-0ef452dc0fb1
definitions.locDescription: Increases magazine capacity, allowing more shots before reloading.

definitions.name: 92cece94-cc3a-4a73-b4ea-b52462ba0404
definitions.locDescription: Capacitor boosts kinetic coil generators, increasing shot penetration through solid objects.

definitions.name: b0a2c013-e791-4c20-9e7a-05e865bfbcaa
definitions.locDescription: Simple optical scope to enhance stability while zoomed. Also increases accuracy while moving.

definitions.name: cba4010d-8ff7-44b7-a4a8-47a3095ab755
definitions.locDescription: Enhances a weapon's barrel, creating greater gunfire velocity and impact.

definitions.name: 667103cd-ba43-4903-8c4c-0c7b098137fb
definitions.locDescription: Adjustable servo motors tighten or loosen pellet spread for maximum accuracy.

definitions.name: b93fa0fe-b704-4ee2-a78f-d11a5ea166d9
definitions.locDescription: Adds sockets to increase thermal clip capacity, increasing number of spare shots.

definitions.name: 790352cc-9444-4d28-ad9b-4a162492a322
definitions.locDescription: Enhances a weapon's barrel, creating greater gunfire velocity and impact.

definitions.locDescription: Simple optical scope to enhance stability while zoomed. Also increases accuracy while moving.

definitions.locDescription: Adds sockets to increase thermal clip capacity, increasing number of spare shots.

definitions.locDescription: Superior lightweight alloys replace weapon parts, making the weapon less obtrusive and easier to handle.
